00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:12,480
alluded to at the beginning, 
not necessarily software first,  

305
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:16,480
product first companies. Feels 
like it's very common in banks  

306
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:21,280
and telecom companies and companies that 
aren't product First and software first.

307
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:24,320
There are SaaS companies that do 
Scrum out there and they like it,  

308
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:27,840
and I don't think they're very dogmatic about it.

309
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:28,680
Got it. Yeah.

310
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:33,920
They do it for a reason of just trying to 
